race.comment: CALL ME BASIL (2) led from the outset and demolished a maiden field over this distance at Tuncurry last start. Lightly raced four-year-old with plenty of improvement in store. Can go to this next level and salute again. HIGHLY TEMPTED (3) was in the money two back at Newcastle then struggled in a Class 3 Highway at Rosehill last time. Finds it hard to win but has a decent top three strike rate. Each-way prospects. EDDIE'S CHARM (8) worked home a shade too well to collect her maiden recently over this course and distance. Enjoys all the favours from gate one so despite the class rise another big run is on the cards. TROUNCE (6) came with a well-timed run to win her first race last start over a slightly shorter journey at this track. Has only lined up four times so there should be more in store. GOOD KARMA (10) will be better for this run but might be one for wider exotics.
